						<h2>
							Purchase grid sort - forum features added
							Wednesday, January 28, 2004 - 11:05:52 PM
						</h2>
						<p>
							<P>I have been mostly working on the new forums with the little time I have had to work on guildwizard.&nbsp; I did however sneak in a little feature add on the Purchase View page for DKP guilds.. you can now fully sort the grid...</P>
<P>Here is some of the stuff I added on the new forums today:</P>
<UL>
<LI>Fixed the Member Role, so pages secured by the Members Only permission will work 
<LI>Thread list page will now show unread messages, by popular demand 
<LI>Fixed Sticky and Lock Threads so Officers can do it.. i had it set to Admin account only 
<LI>I fixed a validation problem that was preventing some posts from going through 
<LI>The member list in the Private Message page is now sorted by name to find the recipient name easier 
<LI>Admin/Officer action log is working (this was done yesterday) 
<LI>Fixed a bug which didnt allow Display names if someone in another guild had same Display Name, it now only checks display names in your own guild, the way it`s supposed to. 
<LI>Tuned some indexes on the database.&nbsp; Probably in vein, as I really cant get a good representation of what I should be tuning until more guilds start using the new forums. 
<LI>Locked threads now properly show the locked icon in the thread list (still have to put locked button on message view though) 
<LI>The forum order tool (to re-order your forums in the list) works now 
<LI>The admin grid in the Manage Forums area that shows the forum list with the current security level will now show the description instead of just a number (Will show “Members Only“ instead of &nbsp;“2“)</LI></UL>
<P>The forums are starting to come together.. there is only about 5-6 guilds using them since I deployed them yesterday.. i need about 50 of you guilds to start using them so I can start performance tuning though..&nbsp; </P>
<P>I will continue trying to add the core features of the forums and kill any bugs that I get reported.&nbsp; After the weekend, I anticipate having very little time to do any work on the forums.. I am likely starting on a very large project, which is about a 2 month programming job.&nbsp; That doesn`t mean I wont do anything for two months, it just means I won`t have as much time, as my client is kind of anxious to get this application done (aren`t they all? :)</P>
						</p>
					
